
# 🎭 DeepFake Studio v1.0
**Forensic Deepfake Research & Testing Platform**

> ⚠️ **Authorized Forensic Use Only** — GM Insider Threat Team. Do not distribute output media.

---

## Overview

DeepFake Studio is a PyQt5 desktop application for forensic deepfake generation and detection research. It integrates four state-of-the-art deepfake backends into a unified GUI with drag-and-drop media import, live preview, dependency checking, and session management.

---

## Supported Backends

| Backend | Purpose | Input |
|---|---|---|
| **InsightFace Swap** | Fast face swap via ONNX | Source image + Target image/video |
| **SimSwap** | Identity-preserving face swap with hair/bg masking | Source image + Target image/video |
| **SadTalker** | Audio-driven talking head generation | Source image + Drive audio |
| **FOMM** | Motion-driven face animation | Source image + Driving video |

---

## Requirements

### System
- **OS:** Windows 10/11 (64-bit) — primary platform
- **Python:** 3.10, 3.11, or 3.12 recommended (3.13 has limited wheel support for some deps)
- **RAM:** 8 GB minimum, 16 GB recommended
- **GPU:** Optional — CUDA-capable NVIDIA GPU for faster processing

### Python Packages
See `requirements.txt` for the full list.

Install all dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## External Repositories

Each backend requires cloning a separate repository. Clone them into the project directory:

```bash
# SimSwap
git clone https://github.com/neuralchen/SimSwap

# SadTalker
git clone https://github.com/OpenTalker/SadTalker

# FOMM (First Order Motion Model)
git clone https://github.com/AliaksandrSiarohin/first-order-model
```

---

## Model Files

Download each model file and place it in the correct location:

### InsightFace
| File | Destination | Download |
|---|---|---|
| `inswapper_128.onnx` | Project root or configure path in UI | [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co/ezioruan/inswapper_128.onnx) |
| `GFPGANv1.4.pth` *(optional enhancement)* | Project root | [Google Drive](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1TbIHSHB50vDeRkX3RNs48GcKT1WwjHj3/view) |

### SimSwap
| File | Destination |
|---|---|
| `latest_net_G.pth` | `SimSwap/checkpoints/people/` |
| `arcface_checkpoint.tar` | `SimSwap/arcface_model/` |
| `scrfd_10g_bnkps.onnx` | `SimSwap/insightface_func/models/antelope/` |
| `glintr100.onnx` | `SimSwap/insightface_func/models/antelope/` |
| `79999_iter.pth` | `SimSwap/parsing_model/checkpoint/` |

Download links: [SimSwap Google Drive](https://github.com/neuralchen/SimSwap/issues/255)

### SadTalker
| File | Destination |
|---|---|
| `SadTalker_V0.0.2_256.safetensors` | `SadTalker/checkpoints/` |
| `mapping_00109-model.pth.tar` | `SadTalker/checkpoints/` |
| `mapping_00229-model.pth.tar` | `SadTalker/checkpoints/` |
| `GFPGANv1.4.pth` | `SadTalker/gfpgan/weights/` |

Use gdown to download:
```bash
pip install gdown
python -c "
import gdown
files = {
    'SadTalker/checkpoints/SadTalker_V0.0.2_256.safetensors': '1uweTnhMsV5LRJJK46aaEFWHFWfkm4nY',
    'SadTalker/checkpoints/mapping_00109-model.pth.tar':       '1hSSWJFpRPMGZXvPRfFJHBp2Y5nHWOHSV',
    'SadTalker/checkpoints/mapping_00229-model.pth.tar':       '1mlswlDX2bKHUGdyo5lBnQjA5YMnFbVsm',
    'SadTalker/gfpgan/weights/GFPGANv1.4.pth':                '1TbIHSHB50vDeRkX3RNs48GcKT1WwjHj3',
}
for path, fid in files.items():
    gdown.download(f'https://drive.google.com/uc?id={fid}', path, quiet=False)
"
```

### FOMM
| File | Destination |
