## Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone this repo
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd DeepFake_Studio

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows
# source .venv/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Clone external backends
git clone https://github.com/neuralchen/SimSwap
git clone https://github.com/OpenTalker/SadTalker
git clone https://github.com/AliaksandrSiarohin/first-order-model

# 5. Download model files (see Model Files section above)

# 6. Run
python main_v1.1.py
```

---

## Quick Start Workflow

1. **Import** — Drag & drop a source face image into the Source zone
2. **Import** — Drag & drop a target video/image (InsightFace/SimSwap/FOMM) or drive audio (SadTalker)
3. **Configure** — Select the algorithm tab and set the repository/model path
4. **Export** — Set the output file path
5. **Run** — Click **▶ Run Pipeline**

---

## Known Windows Issues & Fixes

### WinError 1114 — c10.dll initialization failure
PyQt5 and cv2 load their own OpenMP DLLs before torch, causing c10.dll to fail. The app pre-loads torch DLLs at startup to prevent this. If it still occurs:
```bash
set KMP_DUPLICATE_LIB_OK=TRUE
python main_v1.1.py
```

### NumPy 2.x compatibility
SimSwap and SadTalker were written for NumPy 1.x. The app patches deprecated aliases (`np.float`, `np.int`, etc.) automatically at runtime.

### basicsr / gfpgan on Python 3.13
NumPy 1.x wheels don't exist for Python 3.13. Install basicsr from GitHub:
```bash
pip install "git+https://github.com/XPixelGroup/BasicSR.git" --no-build-isolation
pip install gfpgan
```

### SimSwap `models/` not found
Ensure you cloned the full SimSwap repository. Partial downloads/extractions missing the `models/` folder will cause import errors.

---

## GPU Support

The app runs CPU-only by default. To enable GPU:

```bash
# Uninstall CPU versions
pip uninstall onnxruntime torch torchvision -y

# Install GPU versions (adjust cu121 to match your CUDA version)
pip install onnxruntime-gpu
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
```

Then in the UI:
- **InsightFace tab** → check **Use GPU**
- **SimSwap/SadTalker/FOMM** → GPU is used automatically when available

